SUMMARY: Newcomer Youth Career Start Program - Starting February 16 2026
DESCRIPTION:Newcomer Youth Career Start (NYCS) Program\n\nReady to kickst
 art your career in Canada?\n\nWoodgreen is excited to announce that we wi
 ll be starting a new NYCS cohort on February 16\, 2026. NYCS is a hands-o
 n program designed to help newcomer youth (ages 18–29) build job skills\,
  gain confidence\, and get ready to work!\n\nLocation: 2206 Eglinton Aven
 ue East\, Scarborough\, ON M1L 4S8\n\nWhat’s in the Program?\n\n· 2 Weeks
  of Job-Readiness Training:\n\no Learn everything you need to know to sta
 rt working in Canada.\n\n· Life skills workshops:\n\no Workplace Communic
 ation\, Conflict Resolution\, Time Management\, Dress for Success\n\n· On
 e-on-One Support:\n\no Work with an Employment Consultant who will provid
 e guidance and wraparound support\n\n· Job Search & Tool Development:\n\n
 o Resume\, Interview Skills\, LinkedIn\n\nWho Can Join?\n\n✅ You’re 18–29
  years old\n✅ Must be a Permanent Resident\, Conventional Refugee or Prot
 ected Person\n✅ You’re out of school and out of work\n✅ You have a Canadi
 an Language Benchmark (CLB) of 5 or higher\n\nIf you have any inquiries o
 r questions\, please contact the Work Ready Youth team by phone at 416-40
 5-5212 or via email at workreadyyouth@woodgreen.org mailto:workreadyyouth
 @woodgreen.org mailto:workreadyyouth@woodgreen.org\n\nTo register\, pleas
 e complete the screening form on the following link: forms.cloud.microsof
 t/r/zpRZyQSPbj https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/zpRZyQSPbj https://forms.c
 loud.microsoft/r/zpRZyQSPbj
CATEGORIES:Community
